<!--
Hikou no mizu locale file format:
 * <entry key="translation_key">translation</entry>

Variable translations
---------------------
Entries may include variables to be included in the translation.
By convention, all the variables available for an entry
are listed at the end of the key name:

 * <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}">
Example translation with {variable2} and {variable}
</entry>

{variable} will then be replaced in-game by the relevant value.

Context-dependent translations
------------------------------
In case the translation depends on the context, specific translations may be
provided for specific variable values:

 * <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}">
A default translation must always be provided first
</entry>

 * <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}" rounds_count="1">
Specific translation for cases when [rounds_count = 1]
</entry>

Precedence rules
----------------
The selected translation will be the translation with, in decreasing priority:
 - The most number of matching specified variables
 - The least number of unmatched specified variables
 - The highest entry in the list

For example, provided three rules, declared in this order:
 (default: <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}">...</entry>)
  A: <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}" variable2="16">...</entry>
  B: <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}" variable1="8" variable2="16">...</entry>
  C: <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}" variable1="8">...</entry>

* B will be selected for variable1 = 8 and variable2 = 16
* A will be selected for variable1 != 8 and variable2 = 16
* C will be selected for variable1 = 8 and variable2 != 16
* The default translation will be selected for variable1 != 8 and variable2 != 16

If only A and C are listed, as follows:
 (default: <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}">...</entry>)
  A: <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}" variable2="16">...</entry>
  C: <entry key="translation_key:{variable1},{variable2}" variable1="8">...</entry>

In the case where variable1 = 8 and variable2 = 16,
A and C cannot be prioritized based on the number of matches (one each),
nor the number of unmatched rules (0 each).
In turn, the first listed translation, i.e., translation A, will be selected.
-->

